# React Frontend Project Rules

## Stack & Constraints

- React JS only — **no TypeScript** (`.jsx` files only)
- **Frontend only** — no backend, Node.js server, Spring Boot, database, or API integration
- Static dummy data in `data/dummyData.js` (arrays/JSON); use `localStorage` only when persistence is needed
- Avoid unnecessary packages; beginner-friendly, simple, readable code

## React Patterns

- Functional components only; React Hooks (`useState`, `useEffect` when needed)
- Component-based architecture; reusable components in `components/`
- Props for communication; conditional rendering; `map()` for lists
- Forms with validation; loading states when needed; modals/popups done properly
- `react-router-dom` for navigation; semantic HTML
- **Icons rule (strict)**:
  - Use **`react-icons` only** for icons (preferred over custom icon assets)
  - **Do not use SVG icons**: no inline `<svg>`, no `.svg` icon files, no importing `.svg` for icons
  - If an icon is missing, pick the closest `react-icons` alternative instead of adding SVG
  - Keep animations simple

## Naming

- **PascalCase** — components
- **camelCase** — variables
- Meaningful names; no duplicate code; no inline CSS

## Styling

- **Normal CSS only** — separate `.css` files per component/page/layout
- **No Tailwind CSS**
- Global styles: `styles/global.css`, `styles/variables.css`
- Responsive design: Flexbox, CSS Grid, media queries
- Units: `%`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh` when appropriate
- Clean, modern UI; optimized images in `assets/`

## UI & Design (Screenshot-Driven)

- Match shared UI **pixel-perfect**: layout, spacing, colors, fonts, icons, alignment
- Do **not** change design or add extra sections/colors/styles without explicit permission
- UI accuracy over creativity; reuse components
- Stay responsive while preserving the original design
- No horizontal scroll; consistent spacing/alignment across breakpoints
- Navbar, cards, tables, forms must adapt on mobile/tablet/laptop/desktop
- Test common breakpoints; smooth UX on all screen sizes

## Cleanliness & Maintenance

- Delete unused files, components, CSS files, images, and imports
- Remove unused code whenever necessary
- Keep the project clean and optimized
- Do not keep default Vite or React starter files if unused
- Remove unused variables and functions
- Avoid unnecessary folders and packages
- Maintain a clean folder structure

## Structure Preservation (Strict)

- Do not change the existing project structure unless explicitly requested
- Follow the current folder structure consistently
- Do not rename folders or components without permission
- Do not move files to different folders unless requested
- Preserve the existing architecture and code organization
- Any structural changes must be done only after approval
- Continue development using the current structure and patterns

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── assets/
│   ├── images/
│   ├── icons/
│   └── videos/
├── components/
│   ├── Navbar/     (Navbar.jsx, Navbar.css, hooks/useNavbar.js)
│   ├── Footer/
│   ├── Button/
│   └── Card/
├── pages/
│   ├── Home/
│   ├── About/
│   ├── Contact/
│   └── Services/
│   (each: Page.jsx, Page.css, hooks/usePage.js)
├── layouts/
│   ├── MainLayout.jsx
│   └── MainLayout.css
├── routes/
│   └── AppRoutes.jsx
├── shared-hooks/
│   ├── useFetch.js
│   ├── useLocalStorage.js
│   ├── useToggle.js
│   └── useWindowSize.js
├── utils/
│   └── helpers.js
├── data/
│   └── dummyData.js
├── styles/
│   ├── global.css
│   └── variables.css
├── App.jsx
├── App.css
└── main.jsx
```

## Implementation Checklist

- New pages → `pages/`; shared UI → `components/`; routing → `routes/AppRoutes.jsx`
- Wrap pages with `layouts/MainLayout.jsx` (Navbar + Footer)
- Data → import from `data/dummyData.js`; shared logic → `shared-hooks/` or page/component `hooks/`
- Before creating files, check for existing reusable components/hooks
